 the truth might hurt someone. Perhaps a lie would be a better action here. But isn't it always wrong to tell a lie? Well, utilitarians would argue that the widespread practice of lying, even for a good outcome, would result in a loss of trust and securit
\hich\af2\dbch\af12\loch\f2 y\hich\af2\dbch\af12\loch\f2 
 and thus lead to more unhappiness in general. And that's why it's wrong. However, others, defenders of this approach, would argue that there are cases when, yes, it's sometimes right to lie or even to steal. So they would say that if an action, whatever 
