\par 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af12\loch\f2 But, can we really decide if a particular action, with all its unforeseen, unknown, future consequences - can be judged as promoting happiness or not? I'm talking here about e\hich\af2\dbch\af12\loch\f2 
ven simple everyday actions. Surely it's impossible or impractical to judge which actions would bring the least pain and most pleasure. For example, suppose I have a choice between attending an important meeting and attending someone's birthday party. Whi
